### Color Rules

- **Travertine is the dominant surface.** Never use pure `#FFFFFF` as a page background. White is reserved for elevated card surfaces only.
- **Oro (Gold) — use sparingly.** Reserved for: primary CTAs on dark backgrounds, premium badges (Luxury/Exclusive), decorative flourishes, active selection states. Max 3 gold elements per viewport. Never as a large-area background.
- **Conversion-guided hierarchy:** Gold → Obsidian → Terracotta → Neutral. One accent CTA color per screen section.
- **Always pair color with icon + text label.** Never convey meaning through color alone (WCAG 1.4.1). Warning = amber + icon + text, never amber alone.

