### Typography Rules

- Cormorant Garamond is **exclusively for display** (22px+). At 14px it becomes illegible. Use DM Sans for all body copy, UI labels, and functional text.
- Italic Cormorant is used for evocative/editorial emphasis (destination names, taglines).
- Eyebrow/label text: DM Sans 600, 10-11px, `letter-spacing: 0.12em`, `text-transform: uppercase`, color terracotta.
- Secondary/muted text color: `#7A7060` or `#B5A890`.

