## Developer Implementation

### Naming Conventions
- **CSS tokens:** kebab-case with semantic intent: `--color-[name]`, `--space-[n]`
- **Component classes:** BEM-inspired: `.destination-card__title`, `.btn--gold`
- **JS state:** data attributes for hooks: `data-state="open"`, never class-only state

### Dark Mode Strategy
- Use CSS custom property overrides within `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` and `[data-theme="dark"]` for manual toggle.
- All color tokens reference semantic names. Swap the token values, not the components.

### Accessibility Checklist
- All interactive elements: visible focus rings (2px oro outline)
- Minimum touch target: 44x44px (Apple HIG standard)
- Color contrast: 4.5:1 AA minimum for all body text
- All images: descriptive alt attributes
- Semantic HTML: `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, landmark roles
- Form fields: labels linked via `for`/`id`
- Error messages: `aria-live="polite"` regions
- Accordion: `aria-expanded`, `aria-controls` pairs
- Modals: focus trap, `Escape` key dismissal

### Performance & Images
- Hero images: AVIF → WebP → JPEG fallback chain
- Lazy load all below-fold images with native `loading="lazy"`
- Art direction: `<picture>` with mobile-optimized crops
- LCP target: hero image ≤ 2.5s on 4G mobile
- Fonts: `font-display: swap`, preload critical weights only
- Subset fonts to Latin + Latin-Extended for multilingual
- Motion: respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

### Multilingual Considerations
- **Text expansion:** German/Finnish expand English by 35%. Use flexible containers. Test all labels with German copy. Buttons must wrap gracefully.
- **RTL (Arabic):** Use logical CSS properties (`margin-inline-start` not `margin-left`). Set `dir="rtl"` on `<html>`, use `:dir(rtl)` selectors.
- **Font fallbacks:** Cormorant has no Arabic/CJK glyphs. Arabic → `Noto Sans Arabic`; Japanese → `Noto Serif JP`.
- **Supported languages:** EN, IT, DE, FR, ES, AR (+ Mandarin/Japanese on request).
